  "response": "If you want a smartphone that keeps you active on Messenger (or other apps) reliably using mobile data, here are some key features to look for:\n\n### 1. **Battery Life**\n   - A phone with a **large battery capacity** (4000mAh or more) ensures it lasts all day.\n   - Phones with **battery optimization** features (e.g., adaptive battery) help conserve power.\n\n   **Examples:**\n   - **iPhone 15 Plus** (4323mAh, excellent standby time)\n   - **Samsung Galaxy A54** (5000mAh)\n   - **Xiaomi Redmi Note 12 Pro** (5000mAh)\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Data Efficiency**\n   - Look for phones that support **5G** for faster and more reliable data connections.\n   - Phones with **dual SIM** (or eSIM) let you switch to a better mobile data provider if needed.\n\n   **Examples:**\n   - **Google Pixel 7a** (5G, efficient Android OS)\n   - **OnePlus Nord CE 3 Lite** (5G, affordable)\n   - **Samsung Galaxy S23 FE** (5G, excellent performance)\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Performance**\n   - A phone with a **decent processor** and **sufficient RAM** (4GB or more) ensures smooth multitasking.\n   - Phones with **lightweight operating systems** (e.g., stock Android) are less likely to hog resources.\n\n   **Examples:**\n   - **Motorola Moto G Power (2023)** (efficient, affordable)\n   - **Samsung Galaxy A14 5G** (good budget option)\n   - **iPhone SE (3rd Gen)** (efficient iOS, long-lasting)\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Software Updates**\n   - Phones with **long software support** ensure you stay updated with the latest app and OS optimizations.\n   - **iOS devices** (e.g., iPhones) are known for long-term support.\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Affordable Options**\n   If you\u2019re on a budget, consider:\n   - **Xiaomi Redmi 12C** (large battery, affordable)\n   - **Tecno Spark 10 Pro** (5000mAh, budget-friendly)\n   - **Nokia G21** (long battery life, clean Android)\n\n---\n\n### Tips for Staying Active on Messenger:\n1. **Enable Background Data**: Allow Messenger to run in the background for notifications.\n2. **Use Data-Saving Mode**: Activate Messenger\u2019s data-saving feature in app settings.\n3. **Optimize Battery Usage**: Exclude Messenger from battery optimization to prevent it from being closed.\n4. **Switch to Wi-Fi When Available**: Save mobile data for when you\u2019re on the go.\n\nLet me know your budget or preferences, and I can suggest more tailored options!",
